column2: search for japanese restaurants with at least NUMBER_0 reviews .
column3: @org.schema.Restaurant . Restaurant ( ) filter aggregateRating . reviewCount >= NUMBER_0 && servesCuisine =~ " japanese " ;

column2: list indian restaurants with higher ratings that NUMBER_0 stars .
column3: @org.schema.Restaurant . Restaurant ( ) filter aggregateRating . ratingValue >= NUMBER_0 && servesCuisine =~ " indian " ;

column2: look for a american restaurant that is the closest to me .
column3: ( [ * , distance ( geo , $location . current_location ) ] of sort ( distance ( geo , $location . current_location ) asc of @org.schema.Restaurant . Restaurant ( ) filter servesCuisine =~ " american " ) ) [ 1 ] ;

column2: what 's the telephone number of the the baltimore symphony orchestra on LOCATION_0 ?
column3: [ telephone ] of @org.schema.Restaurant . Restaurant ( ) filter geo == LOCATION_0 && name =~ " the baltimore symphony orchestra " ;

column2: what is the closest italian restaurant with at least a NUMBER_0 star rating ?
column3: ( [ * , distance ( geo , $location . current_location ) ] of sort ( distance ( geo , $location . current_location ) asc of @org.schema.Restaurant . Restaurant ( ) filter any ( @org.schema.Restaurant . Review ( ) filter in_array ( id , review ) && reviewRating . ratingValue == NUMBER_0 ) && servesCuisine =~ " italian " ) ) [ 1 ] ;
